The paper focuses on the security implications of multi-user support in Android, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of the new features and their impact on the operating system, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE) and operating systems (cs.OS). The methodology used to identify vulnerabilities and privacy issues could be considered under systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
